The paper deals with geometric data structures for temporal point sets and their querying. This falls under the domain of computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses proximity relations and skyline queries, which are relevant to database systems (cs.DB). The use of data structures for efficient querying is also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper's focus on time-windowed querying makes it relevant to temporal databases and systems (cs.SI).
